  "texts": [
    "This affected the comparability of the studies and introduced heterogeneity in the results of burnout prevalence.",
    "Most studies had limited participants and no comparative control group, making it impossible to confirm any identified associations.",
    "Non-response and selection bias was rampant across the included studies.",
    "Varying locations, differing programme structures and studies involving participants from only one training centre reduced the generalisability of the results.",
    "This review did not consider other important variables associated with burnout such as work hours and environment or personal circumstances."
